ierungen reichte es von radikalen Anhängern der Turnerbewegung bis in hohe Berliner Regierungskreise.  aThe revised 1st volume of the historical-critical complete edition of the correspondence of Leopold von Ranke contains 274 letters written by him and to him. For the first time, a basic new commentary reconstructs the young Ranke’s broad network of relationships, thereby offering new insights into the career strategies of the most important German-language historian of the 19th century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aGeschichtsschreibung. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aHistoriography. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLeopold von Ranke. 4aWissenschaftsgeschichte. 4acultural history. 4ahistory of science. 4ahistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aGrypa, Dietmar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHistorische Kommission, , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2016z9783110485189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104121470 cprintz978348659005040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311041212340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110412123423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110412123.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016